      "date": "2019-11-25 20:42:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nI have one idea, but it doesn't necessarily have to be in this patch. I was thinking it would be useful to keep track of the number of times a peer has been discovered. Currently we have no way of separating discovery traffic from standard traffic on the peer. If we do add that stat, it can be used to also determine if a discovery attempt has been made.",
